IX-Breath
Copyright 2026 Bryce Lovell

This repository contains original architecture, requirements, safety, validation,
and design-synthesis material for IX-Breath, a rescue-biased regenerative portable
life support system (PLSS) architecture study for delayed-ingress astronaut survival.

Portions of the systems-engineering approach in this repository were developed from
earlier concept exploration by Bryce Lovell. IX-Breath retains only the bounded,
real-world engineering patterns explicitly documented in this repository.

